(firstQuint)Clinical Evaluation of Patients With X-linked Retinoschisis.

 The objective of the study is to evaluate subjects with XLRS in a clinical setting and gather data on disease progression.

 The data from this study will enhance the understanding of the natural history of this rare disease and will facilitate appropriately powered safety studies in a future gene therapy trial in humans.

